00:17:04.357 --> 00:17:06.058 align:middle line:90%
oh gosh, lots of different.

00:17:06.058 --> 00:17:08.493 align:middle line:90%
Liberace's come through me.

00:17:08.493 --> 00:17:10.695 align:middle line:90%
Lots of people, lots of people.

00:17:10.695 --> 00:17:12.964 align:middle line:90%
Do you have to kind of turn on,

00:17:12.964 --> 00:17:14.634 align:middle line:90%
for lack of a better word,

00:17:14.634 --> 00:17:16.368 align:middle line:90%
the ability to hear these?

00:17:16.368 --> 00:17:18.704 align:middle line:84%
Or else you would be barraged
all day long?

00:17:18.704 --> 00:17:20.940 align:middle line:84%
Yes, and part of learning how
to do this work

00:17:20.940 --> 00:17:23.643 align:middle line:84%
in development is learning how
to turn on, turn off.

00:17:23.643 --> 00:17:25.278 align:middle line:90%
So, it's like a radio station.

00:17:25.278 --> 00:17:26.646 align:middle line:84%
You have a radio, your turn the
radio on

00:17:26.646 --> 00:17:28.114 align:middle line:90%
you tune into a station.

00:17:28.114 --> 00:17:29.048 align:middle line:90%
That's like me.

00:17:29.048 --> 00:17:30.850 align:middle line:84%
I turn on, I put myself in a
receptive space

00:17:30.850 --> 00:17:32.818 align:middle line:84%
and then I kind of tune into
the whispers,

00:17:32.818 --> 00:17:34.086 align:middle line:90%
the subtle whispers.

00:17:34.086 --> 00:17:36.589 align:middle line:84%
the feelings, the emotions that
I'm receiving

00:17:36.589 --> 00:17:37.957 align:middle line:90%
and I give them out.

00:17:37.957 --> 00:17:39.191 align:middle line:84%
When I'm finished doing the
work,

00:17:39.191 --> 00:17:40.526 align:middle line:90%
I kind of shut down.

00:17:40.526 --> 00:17:42.094 align:middle line:84%
I take away the awareness and
then

00:17:42.094 --> 00:17:43.329 align:middle line:90%
I'm back to normal.

00:17:43.329 --> 00:17:44.463 align:middle line:90%
An everyday person.

00:17:44.463 --> 00:17:46.465 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting because I
measure it

00:17:46.465 --> 00:17:48.968 align:middle line:84%
based on the amount of truth I
feel.

00:17:48.968 --> 00:17:50.836 align:middle line:84%
When I heard or I saw the piece
where

00:17:50.836 --> 00:17:52.738 align:middle line:90%
Farrah Fawcett came through you,

00:17:52.738 --> 00:17:54.040 align:middle line:84%
instead of talking about the
fact that

00:17:54.040 --> 00:17:56.142 align:middle line:84%
she died on the same day as
Michael Jackson.

00:17:56.142 --> 00:17:57.643 align:middle line:90%
Yes, yes.

00:17:57.643 --> 00:17:59.245 align:middle line:84%
There were little things when
Farrah Fawcett came through,

00:17:59.245 --> 00:18:03.416 align:middle line:84%
little subtleties, which, being
the voice box basically

00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:04.817 align:middle line:84%
I never know what's going to
come through

00:18:04.817 --> 00:18:05.885 align:middle line:90%
or what they're going to say.

00:18:05.885 --> 00:18:07.887 align:middle line:84%
The personalities really come
through.

00:18:07.887 --> 00:18:09.722 align:middle line:84%
I remember that she was talking
about

00:18:09.722 --> 00:18:12.625 align:middle line:84%
a bracelet she'd given her
friend and

00:18:12.625 --> 00:18:14.460 align:middle line:84%
she was actually wearing the
bracelet.

00:18:14.460 --> 00:18:15.728 align:middle line:84%
She talked about being upset
because

00:18:15.728 --> 00:18:18.130 align:middle line:84%
Michael Jackson died around the
same time she did.

00:18:18.130 --> 00:18:20.232 align:middle line:90%
Same day, yeah.

00:18:20.232 --> 00:18:21.434 align:middle line:84%
So much publicity for him, a
little for her

00:18:21.434 --> 00:18:23.102 align:middle line:84%
but she was very understanding
but--

00:18:23.102 --> 00:18:23.836 align:middle line:90%
(laughter)

00:18:23.836 --> 00:18:25.805 align:middle line:84%
Alana Stewart. Alana Stewart
had had the reading.

00:18:25.805 --> 00:18:28.074 align:middle line:84%
She was wearing the bracelet
that she gave her

00:18:28.074 --> 00:18:29.675 align:middle line:90%
and Farrah mentioned it.

00:18:29.675 --> 00:18:31.143 align:middle line:90%
"You're wearing my bracelet."

00:18:31.143 --> 00:18:36.148 align:middle line:84%
When somebody crosses over or
moves on as spirit,

00:18:37.283 --> 00:18:40.519 align:middle line:84%
do they really want to come
through and communicate

00:18:40.519 --> 00:18:43.055 align:middle line:84%
with the person who is still on
this Earth plane

00:18:43.055 --> 00:18:45.524 align:middle line:84%
when they really have an
attachment to someone?

00:18:45.524 --> 00:18:47.293 align:middle line:84%
Like losing a father or a child
even?

00:18:47.293 --> 00:18:49.628 align:middle line:90%
Just like the movie, "Ghost,"

00:18:49.628 --> 00:18:51.230 align:middle line:84%
which I think is a wonderful
depiction

00:18:51.230 --> 00:18:52.765 align:middle line:90%
of how it really is,

00:18:52.765 --> 00:18:54.600 align:middle line:10%
when you leave this physical
shell which

00:18:54.600 --> 00:18:57.036 align:middle line:10%
is very painless, there's no
pain involved

00:18:57.036 --> 00:18:59.438 align:middle line:10%
with leaving the body, no pain
whatsoever.

00:18:59.438 --> 00:19:01.207 align:middle line:10%
Leading up to the death, there
might be some pain

00:19:01.207 --> 00:19:03.976 align:middle line:10%
involved with the type of way
you pass out,

00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:05.277 align:middle line:90%
but when you actually leave,

00:19:05.277 --> 00:19:06.545 align:middle line:84%
when the spirit leaves the
physical body,

00:19:06.545 --> 00:19:07.813 align:middle line:90%
there is no pain.

00:19:07.813 --> 00:19:09.115 align:middle line:84%
One of the first things they
want to do is

00:19:09.115 --> 00:19:10.116 align:middle line:90%
to tell their loved ones,

00:19:10.116 --> 00:19:12.585 align:middle line:90%
"I'm okay, I'm alive, I'm fine.

00:19:12.585 --> 00:19:14.186 align:middle line:90%
"You don't need to grieve.

00:19:14.186 --> 00:19:15.488 align:middle line:90%
"You don't need to be upset,

00:19:15.488 --> 00:19:17.923 align:middle line:84%
"Don't be upset about my death
because I'm not dead.

00:19:17.923 --> 00:19:19.492 align:middle line:90%
"I'm very alive."

00:19:19.492 --> 00:19:20.760 align:middle line:84%
And they all go to their
funerals.

00:19:20.760 --> 00:19:22.762 align:middle line:84%
They all go to their funerals,
their memorial services.

00:19:22.762 --> 00:19:25.798 align:middle line:84%
They'll see who is standing in
the funeral chapel there.

00:19:25.798 --> 00:19:26.799 align:middle line:90%
All the time.

00:19:26.799 --> 00:19:27.733 align:middle line:84%
I can imagine that would be
healing because

00:19:27.733 --> 00:19:30.302 align:middle line:84%
if you have someone who maybe
died a painful death

00:19:30.302 --> 00:19:33.539 align:middle line:84%
or a disease or an illness and
you watch their physical body

00:19:33.539 --> 00:19:35.708 align:middle line:90%
go through such pain,

00:19:35.708 --> 00:19:37.977 align:middle line:84%
to imagine them no longer in
that pain

00:19:37.977 --> 00:19:40.346 align:middle line:90%
it takes a leap of faith.

00:19:40.346 --> 00:19:42.848 align:middle line:84%
It does but a lot of times,
spirit will come back and say,

00:19:42.848 --> 00:19:45.051 align:middle line:84%
"Mom, please don't remember me
that way.

00:19:45.051 --> 00:19:46.619 align:middle line:90%
"I'm not in that car crash.

00:19:46.619 --> 00:19:48.354 align:middle line:84%
"Mom, that's not my body like
that,

00:19:48.354 --> 00:19:50.856 align:middle line:84%
"that's withered and dried up
like that.

00:19:50.856 --> 00:19:52.058 align:middle line:90%
"That's not who I am.

00:19:52.058 --> 00:19:53.426 align:middle line:84%
"Don't remember me that way
because

00:19:53.426 --> 00:19:54.360 align:middle line:90%
"that's not who I was.

00:19:54.360 --> 00:19:58.330 align:middle line:84%
"That was the old me, I'm the
young vital person now.

00:19:58.330 --> 00:19:59.498 align:middle line:90%
"That's my spirit."

00:19:59.498 --> 00:20:00.999 align:middle line:90%
The spirit is very very young.

00:20:00.999 --> 00:20:02.968 align:middle line:84%
We all go back to the younger
part of our lives,

00:20:02.968 --> 00:20:04.103 align:middle line:90%
the prime of our lives.

00:20:04.103 --> 00:20:04.970 align:middle line:90%
We do?

00:20:04.970 --> 00:20:07.807 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, let's say we die when
we're 70 or 80 or 90s.

00:20:07.807 --> 00:20:09.842 align:middle line:84%
You tend to go back to the
prime of your life,

00:20:09.842 --> 00:20:11.811 align:middle line:84%
the time of your life that you
liked the most.

00:20:11.811 --> 00:20:14.847 align:middle line:84%
Most people tend to go back to
their 20s or their 30s.

00:20:14.847 --> 00:20:16.649 align:middle line:90%
This is very interesting, Lisa.

00:20:16.649 --> 00:20:18.984 align:middle line:84%
When the spirit does come back
and they will communicate,

00:20:18.984 --> 00:20:21.120 align:middle line:84%
many times they will
communicate in memories,

00:20:21.120 --> 00:20:23.722 align:middle line:84%
very fond memories that the
person receiving

00:20:23.722 --> 00:20:25.424 align:middle line:90%
the information will understand.

00:20:25.424 --> 00:20:27.359 align:middle line:84%
Like, your dad is talking to me
about the lake,

00:20:27.359 --> 00:20:29.028 align:middle line:84%
you used to go to the lake and
have barbecues

00:20:29.028 --> 00:20:29.895 align:middle line:90%
in July and August.

00:20:29.895 --> 00:20:31.163 align:middle line:90%
Yes we used to do that.

00:20:31.163 --> 00:20:33.933 align:middle line:84%
And he's talking about ride in
the boat.

00:20:33.933 --> 00:20:36.469 align:middle line:84%
Yes, we used to do that, those
were great memories.

00:20:36.469 --> 00:20:37.937 align:middle line:84%
That's what he's going to bring
through.

00:20:37.937 --> 00:20:39.205 align:middle line:84%
So, they often come back that
way.

00:20:39.205 --> 00:20:40.206 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that makes sense and

00:20:40.206 --> 00:20:42.341 align:middle line:84%
I've seen it happen in a room,
too, as well.

00:20:42.341 --> 00:20:44.610 align:middle line:90%
So, when we have those memories,

00:20:44.610 --> 00:20:47.346 align:middle line:90%
if we've lost a loved one,

00:20:47.346 --> 00:20:49.582 align:middle line:84%
can we then communicate to our
loved ones

00:20:49.582 --> 00:20:50.816 align:middle line:90%
through those memories?

00:20:50.816 --> 00:20:51.984 align:middle line:90%
Yes, we can.

00:20:51.984 --> 00:20:53.619 align:middle line:84%
There's easy ways to
communicate with spirit.

00:20:53.619 --> 00:20:56.122 align:middle line:84%
People think you need a medium
to do it.

00:20:56.122 --> 00:20:56.889 align:middle line:90%
Not necessarily.

00:20:56.889 --> 00:20:58.958 align:middle line:84%
A medium is someone who is able
to hear them clearly

00:20:58.958 --> 00:21:01.327 align:middle line:84%
and really be able to translate
what they're saying,

00:21:01.327 --> 00:21:03.896 align:middle line:84%
translate the images, the
impressions,

00:21:03.896 --> 00:21:05.998 align:middle line:84%
but everybody can hear from
their loved ones.

00:21:05.998 --> 00:21:08.267 align:middle line:84%
For instance, if you go to
sleep at night,

00:21:08.267 --> 00:21:10.069 align:middle line:84%
ask that they come to you in
your dreams.

00:21:10.069 --> 00:21:11.437 align:middle line:84%
That's the number one way they
communicate

00:21:11.437 --> 00:21:13.305 align:middle line:84%
is the dream state so they'll
come through your dreams.

00:21:13.305 --> 00:21:14.740 align:middle line:90%
You'll have a dream of them.

00:21:14.740 --> 00:21:16.175 align:middle line:84%
Or keep a journal next to your
bed.

00:21:16.175 --> 00:21:19.278 align:middle line:84%
Try to meditate and quiet your
mind and listen to them.

00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:21.380 align:middle line:84%
They'll start writing a message
to you.

00:21:21.380 --> 00:21:22.948 align:middle line:84%
Why would they come through our
dreams?

00:21:22.948 --> 00:21:25.151 align:middle line:84%
It's the easiest way to get
through because

00:21:25.151 --> 00:21:27.386 align:middle line:84%
we're not on our rational
conscious mind.

00:21:27.386 --> 00:21:28.921 align:middle line:90%
We're not in the critical mind.

00:21:28.921 --> 00:21:30.189 align:middle line:84%
That little mind chatter that
says

00:21:30.189 --> 00:21:31.757 align:middle line:90%
"Oh, this can't possibly be."

00:21:31.757 --> 00:21:33.826 align:middle line:84%
That little left brain, that
left part that's

00:21:33.826 --> 00:21:35.895 align:middle line:84%
analyzing, critiquing
everything.

00:21:35.895 --> 00:21:36.996 align:middle line:90%
We're not in that space.

00:21:36.996 --> 00:21:40.199 align:middle line:84%
We're away from that so it's
easy to drop something in.

00:21:40.199 --> 00:21:42.935 align:middle line:84%
So, we're not in a place of
being able to move, either,

00:21:42.935 --> 00:21:45.337 align:middle line:90%
so our minds are pretty clear.

00:21:45.337 --> 00:21:49.675 align:middle line:84%
I mean, one of the wonderful
reasons I'd love

00:21:49.675 --> 00:21:51.510 align:middle line:84%
to have you on the show and
you're here,

00:21:51.510 --> 00:21:54.613 align:middle line:84%
so that people who are in that
space of grief

00:21:54.613 --> 00:21:56.782 align:middle line:84%
can get some communication and
maybe

00:21:56.782 --> 00:21:58.751 align:middle line:90%
try some things on their own.

00:21:58.751 --> 00:22:01.420 align:middle line:90%
That's why I love what you do.

00:22:01.420 --> 00:22:04.690 align:middle line:84%
People try this in the privacy
of their own home

00:22:04.690 --> 00:22:06.525 align:middle line:90%
in their quietest hours.

00:22:06.525 --> 00:22:07.927 align:middle line:90%
"I heard this person talk and

00:22:07.927 --> 00:22:10.296 align:middle line:84%
"maybe this works so maybe I'll
try this."

00:22:10.296 --> 00:22:12.364 align:middle line:84%
They have to be consistent
about it.

00:22:12.364 --> 00:22:13.265 align:middle line:90%
You can't be like

00:22:13.265 --> 00:22:15.301 align:middle line:84%
"I'm going to do this tonight
and have results right away."

00:22:15.301 --> 00:22:16.202 align:middle line:90%
No, no, no.

00:22:16.202 --> 00:22:18.904 align:middle line:84%
It's really a process and it's
a process of,

00:22:18.904 --> 00:22:22.041 align:middle line:84%
if you will, training the mind
also to be open.

00:22:22.041 --> 00:22:25.511 align:middle line:84%
A lot of us have a lot of
trouble quieting the mind.

00:22:25.511 --> 00:22:27.646 align:middle line:84%
So, you have to train the mind
to quiet the mind.

00:22:27.646 --> 00:22:29.114 align:middle line:84%
The more you do it, the better
you get it at.

00:22:29.114 --> 00:22:31.083 align:middle line:84%
Another great exercise I have
people do

00:22:31.083 --> 00:22:32.885 align:middle line:84%
is to write a letter to their
loved one.

00:22:32.885 --> 00:22:35.087 align:middle line:90%
Sit down and physically write.

00:22:35.087 --> 00:22:36.822 align:middle line:84%
Letter writing has gone out for
the computer,

00:22:36.822 --> 00:22:38.657 align:middle line:84%
but I think that it's wonderful
when you can

00:22:38.657 --> 00:22:40.359 align:middle line:84%
take the time and the energy to
sit and

00:22:40.359 --> 00:22:41.961 align:middle line:90%
write them a love letter.

00:22:41.961 --> 00:22:46.365 align:middle line:84%
A letter, just a note, what you
want to think about them,

00:22:46.365 --> 00:22:47.833 align:middle line:90%
what you want to say to them.

00:22:47.833 --> 00:22:48.901 align:middle line:90%
Then, put that letter away.

00:22:48.901 --> 00:22:50.636 align:middle line:84%
Fold it away, put it in an
envelope

00:22:50.636 --> 00:22:52.471 align:middle line:84%
and put it in your drawer for
probably two weeks.

00:22:52.471 --> 00:22:55.040 align:middle line:84%
In your calendar, write down
"response" and

00:22:55.040 --> 00:22:57.943 align:middle line:84%
then two weeks later you sit
down with a paper

00:22:57.943 --> 00:23:01.146 align:middle line:84%
and let them write a letter to
you and

00:23:01.146 --> 00:23:03.282 align:middle line:84%
I guarantee you people will get
results.

00:23:03.282 --> 00:23:05.985 align:middle line:84%
I have had thousands and
thousands of my clients do this

00:23:05.985 --> 00:23:07.253 align:middle line:90%
and it's a staggering amount

00:23:07.253 --> 00:23:08.721 align:middle line:90%
how many get results right away.

00:23:08.721 --> 00:23:11.123 align:middle line:84%
They'll say, "Wow, I never even
thought it that way."

00:23:11.123 --> 00:23:12.191 align:middle line:90%
It's amazing.

00:23:12.191 --> 00:23:13.259 align:middle line:84%
So, you clear your mind and you
just allow

00:23:13.259 --> 00:23:16.228 align:middle line:84%
the information to come through
as a response?

00:23:16.228 --> 00:23:18.297 align:middle line:90%
Exactly right.

00:23:18.297 --> 00:23:20.866 align:middle line:84%
Another one they can do, and I
teach this in my class,

00:23:20.866 --> 00:23:23.736 align:middle line:84%
is to get into that quiet
space, if you will,

00:23:23.736 --> 00:23:27.539 align:middle line:84%
and just become focused on that
person

00:23:27.539 --> 00:23:29.141 align:middle line:90%
that passed into spirit.

00:23:29.141 --> 00:23:30.909 align:middle line:90%
Just become them.

00:23:30.909 --> 00:23:33.812 align:middle line:84%
Let them use your body, let
your eyes become their eyes,

00:23:33.812 --> 00:23:36.115 align:middle line:84%
your hands become their hands,
your arms their arms

00:23:36.115 --> 00:23:38.817 align:middle line:84%
and let them just take you over
and be.

00:23:38.817 --> 00:23:40.352 align:middle line:90%
Then listen.

00:23:40.352 --> 00:23:42.788 align:middle line:84%
Listen to what comes through in
your mind.

00:23:42.788 --> 00:23:45.357 align:middle line:84%
You'll be amazed at what comes
through.

00:23:45.357 --> 00:23:48.627 align:middle line:84%
The opinions, perspectives on
things change.

00:23:48.627 --> 00:23:50.095 align:middle line:90%
It works really really well

00:23:50.095 --> 00:23:51.697 align:middle line:84%
so it's another way of doing
that.

00:23:51.697 --> 00:23:53.032 align:middle line:90%
There's always ways .

00:23:53.032 --> 00:23:54.166 align:middle line:90%
They're right around us.

00:23:54.166 --> 00:23:55.801 align:middle line:90%
They share the space around us.

00:23:55.801 --> 00:23:58.203 align:middle line:84%
It's just a matter of us
breaking down those walls

00:23:58.203 --> 00:24:00.639 align:middle line:84%
so as to enable them to come
through easier.

00:24:00.639 --> 00:24:02.741 align:middle line:84%
Could you do that even maybe
for someone

00:24:02.741 --> 00:24:05.077 align:middle line:90%
who hasn't passed over?

00:24:05.077 --> 00:24:07.479 align:middle line:84%
Just to get communication with
the spirit in general

00:24:07.479 --> 00:24:11.517 align:middle line:84%
because the perspectives of
spirit must be enormous.

00:24:11.517 --> 00:24:14.086 align:middle line:84%
Yes, you can do that,
especially with people--

00:24:14.086 --> 00:24:15.888 align:middle line:84%
because spirit to spirit can
communicate.

00:24:15.888 --> 00:24:17.189 align:middle line:90%
We're physical beings but

00:24:17.189 --> 00:24:19.091 align:middle line:84%
we're also spirit first and
foremost,

00:24:19.091 --> 00:24:21.226 align:middle line:84%
so the spirit of somebody, you
can certainly

00:24:21.226 --> 00:24:22.895 align:middle line:90%
call for them to come to you,

00:24:22.895 --> 00:24:24.430 align:middle line:90%
someone who's living,

00:24:24.430 --> 00:24:25.497 align:middle line:84%
and you can work with them that
way.

00:24:25.497 --> 00:24:26.465 align:middle line:90%
What is the spirit that--

00:24:26.465 --> 00:24:28.734 align:middle line:84%
the perspective that spirit
usually has?

00:24:28.734 --> 00:24:30.169 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:24:30.169 --> 00:24:33.505 align:middle line:84%
