00:43:02.280 --> 00:43:04.782 align:middle line:90%
I grew up in Bayside, New York,

00:43:04.782 --> 00:43:07.518 align:middle line:84%
which is a suburb of New York
City and

00:43:07.518 --> 00:43:09.821 align:middle line:84%
I was the youngest of four
children.

00:43:09.821 --> 00:43:11.722 align:middle line:90%
I had a sister, Lynn,

00:43:11.722 --> 00:43:12.857 align:middle line:90%
a brother, Michael,

00:43:12.857 --> 00:43:14.826 align:middle line:90%
a sister, Moira and myself.

00:43:14.826 --> 00:43:17.595 align:middle line:84%
I found that my childhood was a
little bit lonely

00:43:17.595 --> 00:43:19.297 align:middle line:90%
in a way when I look back,

00:43:19.297 --> 00:43:24.302 align:middle line:84%
only because I could see things
that other kids could not.

00:43:25.203 --> 00:43:27.238 align:middle line:90%
I think that I was raised,

00:43:27.238 --> 00:43:30.141 align:middle line:84%
I think we are all brought into
this life, on this Earth,

00:43:30.141 --> 00:43:31.476 align:middle line:84%
and we pick our families and
friends.

00:43:31.476 --> 00:43:32.877 align:middle line:90%
I do believe we are soul groups.

00:43:32.877 --> 00:43:34.645 align:middle line:84%
I think we come back in soul
groups and

00:43:34.645 --> 00:43:36.848 align:middle line:84%
I picked a mother who was an
alcoholic.

00:43:36.848 --> 00:43:39.016 align:middle line:84%
So, she had an addiction and as
a child,

00:43:39.016 --> 00:43:42.019 align:middle line:84%
I hated her because I didn't
have a normal childhood

00:43:42.019 --> 00:43:43.955 align:middle line:84%
and I used to wish she was dead
and I used to think

00:43:43.955 --> 00:43:45.656 align:middle line:90%
these horrible things.

00:43:45.656 --> 00:43:49.093 align:middle line:84%
As you grow up and as you
evolve as we all do,

00:43:49.093 --> 00:43:51.629 align:middle line:84%
we look back at things and we
see the lesson.

00:43:51.629 --> 00:43:53.998 align:middle line:90%
Now that I look back, of course,

00:43:53.998 --> 00:43:55.633 align:middle line:90%
my early 20s I think it was,

00:43:55.633 --> 00:43:58.269 align:middle line:84%
actually when she first passed
over,

00:43:58.269 --> 00:44:00.605 align:middle line:84%
I realized that it was a
disease, number one

00:44:00.605 --> 00:44:02.206 align:middle line:84%
and then as I evolved
spiritually,

00:44:02.206 --> 00:44:04.642 align:middle line:84%
getting more aware of what this
stuff is

00:44:04.642 --> 00:44:06.644 align:middle line:84%
all about, that we are spirits
first and foremost

00:44:06.644 --> 00:44:07.979 align:middle line:90%
having a physical experience,

00:44:07.979 --> 00:44:10.281 align:middle line:84%
I realized that I picked that
situation in my life

00:44:10.281 --> 00:44:12.650 align:middle line:84%
as we all do and I picked that
situation because

00:44:12.650 --> 00:44:14.986 align:middle line:84%
I needed someone to teach me
about compassion.

00:44:14.986 --> 00:44:16.420 align:middle line:84%
So, I wouldn't have been able
to do that work

00:44:16.420 --> 00:44:17.989 align:middle line:84%
that I'm doing now without
learning about

00:44:17.989 --> 00:44:20.424 align:middle line:84%
what compassion is and what
better way to learn it

00:44:20.424 --> 00:44:23.094 align:middle line:90%
than from your mother?

00:44:23.094 --> 00:44:25.596 align:middle line:90%
So much pain but so much growth.

00:44:25.596 --> 00:44:27.665 align:middle line:84%
So much growth through the pain
and

00:44:27.665 --> 00:44:29.667 align:middle line:84%
afterwards I realized we've got
to see the bigger picture.

00:44:29.667 --> 00:44:30.902 align:middle line:90%
That was the funny thing.

00:44:30.902 --> 00:44:34.071 align:middle line:84%
She was an incredible, great,
funny woman.

00:44:34.071 --> 00:44:37.475 align:middle line:84%
Great sense of humor, very very
quick, very very witty

00:44:37.475 --> 00:44:40.177 align:middle line:84%
and I think I understood why
she was in that way

00:44:40.177 --> 00:44:42.380 align:middle line:84%
because I think she was also
very psychic,

00:44:42.380 --> 00:44:43.748 align:middle line:90%
very very sensitive.

00:44:43.748 --> 00:44:45.016 align:middle line:84%
She used to get impressions all
the time

00:44:45.016 --> 00:44:46.751 align:middle line:84%
but she didn't know what it was
and

00:44:46.751 --> 00:44:48.085 align:middle line:90%
she was raised Catholic.

00:44:48.085 --> 00:44:49.654 align:middle line:90%
Very Catholic, Irish Catholic.

00:44:49.654 --> 00:44:52.023 align:middle line:84%
I think it was her way to shut
them off,

00:44:52.023 --> 00:44:54.825 align:middle line:84%
shut off the information, the
intuition.

00:44:54.825 --> 00:44:57.028 align:middle line:84%
I also think emotionally she
wasn't getting

00:44:57.028 --> 00:45:00.197 align:middle line:84%
satisfied from the relationship
with my father and

00:45:00.197 --> 00:45:02.800 align:middle line:84%
I think in those days, in that
generation,

00:45:02.800 --> 00:45:04.902 align:middle line:84%
you stayed together, you didn't
divorce.

00:45:04.902 --> 00:45:06.304 align:middle line:84%
There wasn't anything about
divorce.

00:45:06.304 --> 00:45:08.573 align:middle line:84%
I think that was part of it,
too,

00:45:08.573 --> 00:45:10.141 align:middle line:84%
so I think in a way she was
trapped.

00:45:10.141 --> 00:45:12.843 align:middle line:84%
I understand now that was her
way of escape.

00:45:12.843 --> 00:45:16.414 align:middle line:84%
So, I've really got to say to
people that judgement

00:45:16.414 --> 00:45:19.050 align:middle line:90%
is a very bad thing and

00:45:19.050 --> 00:45:21.285 align:middle line:84%
it's a bad thing because number
one,

00:45:21.285 --> 00:45:23.354 align:middle line:84%
people judge because they want
to feel powerful.

00:45:23.354 --> 00:45:25.656 align:middle line:84%
So, if I can judge you, I have
the power and

00:45:25.656 --> 00:45:27.325 align:middle line:90%
I can make you less than I am.

00:45:27.325 --> 00:45:29.026 align:middle line:90%
That's judgement.

00:45:29.026 --> 00:45:31.462 align:middle line:84%
You can't judge anybody because
you don't know

00:45:31.462 --> 00:45:33.531 align:middle line:84%
what their background is, their
back story.

00:45:33.531 --> 00:45:35.232 align:middle line:90%
So, yeah, "Talking to Heaven,"

00:45:35.232 --> 00:45:38.836 align:middle line:84%
that's my life story, in that
as a young child

00:45:38.836 --> 00:45:40.838 align:middle line:84%
I used to see spirits all the
time.

00:45:40.838 --> 00:45:42.473 align:middle line:84%
I used to know things about
people.

00:45:42.473 --> 00:45:44.275 align:middle line:84%
I used to see colors and lights
around people,

00:45:44.275 --> 00:45:46.444 align:middle line:90%
their auras.

00:45:46.444 --> 00:45:47.545 align:middle line:90%
That was my childhood.

00:45:47.545 --> 00:45:51.382 align:middle line:84%
For me, it was great and I just
loved it.

00:45:51.382 --> 00:45:53.017 align:middle line:90%
I was in my own little world and

00:45:53.017 --> 00:45:56.587 align:middle line:84%
people, I said you see these
kids over in the cemetery?

00:45:56.587 --> 00:45:58.756 align:middle line:84%
I was young and playing with
some friends.

00:45:58.756 --> 00:46:00.958 align:middle line:84%
We cut school like good
Catholic boys.

00:46:00.958 --> 00:46:02.026 align:middle line:90%
I said to my friends,

00:46:02.026 --> 00:46:03.527 align:middle line:90%
"You see those two little kids?"

00:46:03.527 --> 00:46:04.562 align:middle line:90%
There were like two year olds,

00:46:04.562 --> 00:46:05.463 align:middle line:90%
playing in the cemetery.

00:46:05.463 --> 00:46:07.264 align:middle line:84%
They said, "What are you
talking about?"

00:46:07.264 --> 00:46:08.699 align:middle line:84%
I said, "Look, there's a boy
and a girl right there

00:46:08.699 --> 00:46:10.368 align:middle line:90%
"next to that headstone."

00:46:10.368 --> 00:46:12.937 align:middle line:84%
We were cutting school and so
we'd go to cemeteries

00:46:12.937 --> 00:46:14.505 align:middle line:90%
for when we'd cut school.

00:46:14.505 --> 00:46:15.406 align:middle line:90%
My friends don't see them.

00:46:15.406 --> 00:46:17.208 align:middle line:84%
I said, "Come on let's look,
let's go over there."

00:46:17.208 --> 00:46:19.543 align:middle line:84%
So, we walked over to the
headstone and

00:46:19.543 --> 00:46:23.080 align:middle line:84%
the two kids went behind it and
that was the end of it.

00:46:23.080 --> 00:46:24.482 align:middle line:90%
I didn't see them anymore.

00:46:24.482 --> 00:46:26.917 align:middle line:84%
We read the headstone and it
was a boy and a girl.

00:46:26.917 --> 00:46:30.521 align:middle line:84%
Brother and sister who died at
the age of three years old.

00:46:30.521 --> 00:46:32.490 align:middle line:84%
But, to me, it was like, it was
normal.

00:46:32.490 --> 00:46:35.960 align:middle line:84%
My childhood has always been a
sense of

00:46:35.960 --> 00:46:38.329 align:middle line:84%
I see spirit, doesn't everybody
see spirit?

00:46:38.329 --> 00:46:39.864 align:middle line:84%
Don't you see the lights around
that person?

00:46:39.864 --> 00:46:41.465 align:middle line:90%
Don't you see their aura?

00:46:41.465 --> 00:46:42.466 align:middle line:90%
You don't see that?

00:46:42.466 --> 00:46:44.235 align:middle line:90%
Come on, you have to see that.

00:46:44.235 --> 00:46:45.936 align:middle line:84%
It was like that sort of thing
and

00:46:45.936 --> 00:46:48.339 align:middle line:84%
I think kids are very open
because you have to remember,

00:46:48.339 --> 00:46:50.675 align:middle line:84%
they just came from the spirit
world,

00:46:50.675 --> 00:46:52.276 align:middle line:84%
so their mindset is really from
that point of view, right?

00:46:52.276 --> 00:46:57.248 align:middle line:84%
Until we drown them around age
eight or nine.

00:46:57.581 --> 00:46:59.216 align:middle line:90%
Oh, no, you don't see that.

00:46:59.216 --> 00:47:02.253 align:middle line:84%
You've got to be smarter than
that.

00:47:02.253 --> 00:47:05.823 align:middle line:84%
That's just fantasy, that's
just imagination.

00:47:05.823 --> 00:47:09.427 align:middle line:84%
It happened in a series of ways
as I think that

00:47:09.427 --> 00:47:12.430 align:middle line:84%
the spirit world was
manipulating it all to happen.

00:47:12.430 --> 00:47:14.598 align:middle line:84%
I do believe that because I
think we are very influenced

00:47:14.598 --> 00:47:16.934 align:middle line:84%
by the other side, no doubt
about it.

00:47:16.934 --> 00:47:19.770 align:middle line:84%
In my childhood, there was a
lady named Connie Leaf,

00:47:19.770 --> 00:47:21.605 align:middle line:84%
who I actually dedicated my
first book to,

00:47:21.605 --> 00:47:23.140 align:middle line:90%
"Talking to Heaven."

