I was eight years old and I was
selling Easter candy

00:47:25.376 --> 00:47:27.445 align:middle line:84%
to the neighbors for Catholic
school

00:47:27.445 --> 00:47:28.813 align:middle line:90%
They used to do that.

00:47:28.813 --> 00:47:30.047 align:middle line:90%
They still do.

00:47:30.047 --> 00:47:31.882 align:middle line:84%
And, I was actually walking
down the street

00:47:31.882 --> 00:47:35.019 align:middle line:84%
and a lady stops with a 1961
Chevy,

00:47:35.019 --> 00:47:36.587 align:middle line:90%
a red convertible and she said,

00:47:36.587 --> 00:47:38.989 align:middle line:84%
"Hey, I have a boy about your
age.

00:47:38.989 --> 00:47:40.124 align:middle line:84%
"We just moved into the
neighborhood.

00:47:40.124 --> 00:47:41.592 align:middle line:84%
"Would you like to come and
meet him?"

00:47:41.592 --> 00:47:43.094 align:middle line:90%
I said, "Yeah."

00:47:43.094 --> 00:47:46.664 align:middle line:84%
You have to remember, this was
a lady and my mother

00:47:46.664 --> 00:47:49.166 align:middle line:84%
was not available and this lady
was so expressive

00:47:49.166 --> 00:47:51.202 align:middle line:90%
and so out there and so bright.

00:47:51.202 --> 00:47:52.369 align:middle line:90%
I was like, whoa.

00:47:52.369 --> 00:47:54.205 align:middle line:90%
She really was my mentor.

00:47:54.205 --> 00:47:55.973 align:middle line:84%
It's always great to see you in
action and

00:47:55.973 --> 00:47:57.742 align:middle line:90%
you're used to being in a room

00:47:57.742 --> 00:48:00.244 align:middle line:84%
and where I see you really
shine is when

00:48:00.244 --> 00:48:01.645 align:middle line:84%
you are in a room like we saw
in that tape

00:48:01.645 --> 00:48:03.714 align:middle line:84%
of giving different people
communication.

00:48:03.714 --> 00:48:05.316 align:middle line:84%
Because there's no one in this
studio right now,

00:48:05.316 --> 00:48:06.884 align:middle line:84%
I want people to be able to see
that.

00:48:06.884 --> 00:48:08.219 align:middle line:90%
It's really great.

00:48:08.219 --> 00:48:11.555 align:middle line:90%
You've also had a lot of shows.

00:48:11.555 --> 00:48:14.058 align:middle line:84%
We talked about earlier that
you were the creator

00:48:14.058 --> 00:48:15.793 align:middle line:90%
of "The Ghost Whisperer,"

00:48:15.793 --> 00:48:17.762 align:middle line:84%
and there's a picture that we
have of you--

00:48:17.762 --> 00:48:19.630 align:middle line:84%
With Jennifer Love Hewitt, my
Jennifer.

00:48:19.630 --> 00:48:21.699 align:middle line:84%
Yes, she was great with that
part, that role.

00:48:21.699 --> 00:48:23.868 align:middle line:84%
She really, I got to meet
Jennifer Love Hewitt,

00:48:23.868 --> 00:48:26.003 align:middle line:84%
we were sitting in a room with
the other producers

00:48:26.003 --> 00:48:27.104 align:middle line:90%
and she said--

00:48:27.104 --> 00:48:28.339 align:middle line:84%
she didn't look at me the whole
time and

00:48:28.339 --> 00:48:29.740 align:middle line:84%
I was like, "Why isn't she
looking at me?"

00:48:29.740 --> 00:48:31.008 align:middle line:90%
She would not look at me.

00:48:31.008 --> 00:48:32.309 align:middle line:84%
Then she came up at the end and
she said,

00:48:32.309 --> 00:48:34.445 align:middle line:84%
"Excuse me, would you have
lunch with me or dinner?"

00:48:34.445 --> 00:48:35.412 align:middle line:90%
I said, "Yeah."

00:48:35.412 --> 00:48:37.047 align:middle line:84%
The next day we had lunch
together and

00:48:37.047 --> 00:48:38.549 align:middle line:90%
I talked to her and I said,

00:48:38.549 --> 00:48:39.416 align:middle line:90%
"Do you know who I am?"

00:48:39.416 --> 00:48:40.284 align:middle line:90%
And she said,

00:48:40.284 --> 00:48:41.886 align:middle line:90%
"Oh, yeah, I'm really a big fan.

00:48:41.886 --> 00:48:43.220 align:middle line:84%
"That's why I couldn't look at
you."

00:48:43.220 --> 00:48:44.889 align:middle line:90%
Okay.

00:48:44.889 --> 00:48:45.589 align:middle line:90%
(laughing)

00:48:45.589 --> 00:48:47.491 align:middle line:84%
And she really, she had a real
curiosity about

00:48:47.491 --> 00:48:49.660 align:middle line:84%
psychic phenomena, life after
death,

00:48:49.660 --> 00:48:51.061 align:middle line:90%
the spirit world,

00:48:51.061 --> 00:48:52.229 align:middle line:90%
So she really loved it.

00:48:52.229 --> 00:48:52.997 align:middle line:90%
Pisces girl

00:48:52.997 --> 00:48:54.198 align:middle line:90%
Very very into this.

00:48:54.198 --> 00:48:57.201 align:middle line:84%
We had a wonderful time helping
her to understand

00:48:57.201 --> 00:48:59.603 align:middle line:84%
my line of work, how the spirit
world works,

00:48:59.603 --> 00:49:01.405 align:middle line:84%
what happens to Earth-bound
spirits.

00:49:01.405 --> 00:49:03.541 align:middle line:84%
She really wanted to know all
about it and

00:49:03.541 --> 00:49:05.342 align:middle line:90%
she was a great great student.

00:49:05.342 --> 00:49:06.177 align:middle line:90%
Good girl.

00:49:06.177 --> 00:49:08.712 align:middle line:84%
Were there miracles that
happened on those sets

00:49:08.712 --> 00:49:10.181 align:middle line:90%
that couldn't be explained?

00:49:10.181 --> 00:49:11.348 align:middle line:90%
Yes. Yes, all the time.

00:49:11.348 --> 00:49:12.850 align:middle line:84%
Can you share some stories with
us?

00:49:12.850 --> 00:49:13.751 align:middle line:90%
Yes, yes.

00:49:13.751 --> 00:49:14.985 align:middle line:90%
I can explain, too.

00:49:14.985 --> 00:49:16.387 align:middle line:90%
We shot at Universal Studios.

00:49:16.387 --> 00:49:17.354 align:middle line:90%
Right around here.

00:49:17.354 --> 00:49:19.023 align:middle line:84%
Right around here, right down
the street.

00:49:19.023 --> 00:49:21.826 align:middle line:84%
A couple things happened which
were just very shocking.

00:49:21.826 --> 00:49:23.527 align:middle line:84%
For me, I'm aware that spirit's
always around

00:49:23.527 --> 00:49:26.096 align:middle line:84%
and they're doing things and
letting things be known

00:49:26.096 --> 00:49:27.264 align:middle line:90%
that they are around.

00:49:27.264 --> 00:49:28.899 align:middle line:84%
The first thing happened in the
editing bay

00:49:28.899 --> 00:49:31.936 align:middle line:84%
that the four editors that we
had on the show,

00:49:31.936 --> 00:49:35.206 align:middle line:84%
their machines would break down
after certain scenes

00:49:35.206 --> 00:49:37.708 align:middle line:84%
and the scenes were when the
spirits were released

00:49:37.708 --> 00:49:40.010 align:middle line:84%
out of the Earth vibration into
the spirit.

00:49:40.010 --> 00:49:41.612 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the show, she'd
release them

00:49:41.612 --> 00:49:43.080 align:middle line:90%
to the higher vibrations.

00:49:43.080 --> 00:49:47.484 align:middle line:84%
It would happen after the first
three or four shows

00:49:47.484 --> 00:49:50.754 align:middle line:84%
that their editing bank would
break,

00:49:50.754 --> 00:49:52.223 align:middle line:84%
the actual machine would break
down,

00:49:52.223 --> 00:49:53.757 align:middle line:84%
right when she released those
spirits.

00:49:53.757 --> 00:49:56.060 align:middle line:84%
It happened four times in the
first season.

00:49:56.060 --> 00:49:58.429 align:middle line:84%
Then we had some spirits who
were there in the room,

00:49:58.429 --> 00:50:01.465 align:middle line:84%
Earth-bound spirits who were
around that whole hallway

00:50:01.465 --> 00:50:03.934 align:middle line:84%
where the editing bay was and
we had to release them.

00:50:03.934 --> 00:50:05.269 align:middle line:90%
So, that was very interesting.

00:50:05.269 --> 00:50:08.005 align:middle line:84%
Another time we had an actor
take his mark

00:50:08.005 --> 00:50:11.041 align:middle line:84%
and it was Jay Mohr and he had
his mark,

00:50:11.041 --> 00:50:13.644 align:middle line:84%
we were rehearsing and he left
that mark

00:50:13.644 --> 00:50:15.646 align:middle line:90%
and a lamp came down and smashed

00:50:15.646 --> 00:50:17.081 align:middle line:90%
right where he was standing.

00:50:17.081 --> 00:50:19.984 align:middle line:84%
So, if he'd been there five
seconds before--

00:50:19.984 --> 00:50:21.018 align:middle line:90%
Oh, right.

00:50:21.018 --> 00:50:23.153 align:middle line:84%
So, we had several of those
types of instances.

00:50:23.153 --> 00:50:24.255 align:middle line:90%
A lot of different things.

00:50:24.255 --> 00:50:27.124 align:middle line:84%
So, you had to actually work
with many different elements.

00:50:27.124 --> 00:50:29.627 align:middle line:84%
I did and I worked a lot with
the writers on the show,

00:50:29.627 --> 00:50:30.861 align:middle line:90%
I worked with the producers.

00:50:30.861 --> 00:50:34.765 align:middle line:84%
I actually did a whole
demonstration for ABC and CBS

00:50:34.765 --> 00:50:36.333 align:middle line:84%
at a producer's house where I
did a demonstration

00:50:36.333 --> 00:50:38.669 align:middle line:84%
to show them that this is very
very real.

00:50:38.669 --> 00:50:41.038 align:middle line:84%
Communication with spirit is a
real thing

00:50:41.038 --> 00:50:42.139 align:middle line:90%
and they were shocked.

00:50:42.139 --> 00:50:43.207 align:middle line:90%
They were very shocked.

00:50:43.207 --> 00:50:45.142 align:middle line:90%
I remember one of the producers,

00:50:45.142 --> 00:50:47.511 align:middle line:84%
it came through that she only
had one kidney

00:50:47.511 --> 00:50:48.579 align:middle line:90%
I think it was.

00:50:48.579 --> 00:50:50.414 align:middle line:90%
No, one ovary, one ovary.

00:50:50.414 --> 00:50:52.116 align:middle line:84%
And her husband didn't even
know it.

00:50:52.116 --> 00:50:53.284 align:middle line:84%
He was sitting right there he
goes,

00:50:53.284 --> 00:50:54.151 align:middle line:90%
"I didn't know that."

00:50:54.151 --> 00:50:56.287 align:middle line:84%
And she says, "Yes, I have only
one ovary."

00:50:56.287 --> 00:50:59.623 align:middle line:90%
It was very good details.

00:50:59.623 --> 00:51:02.226 align:middle line:84%
So, it opens them up to the
realization

00:51:02.226 --> 00:51:04.328 align:middle line:84%
that this is real, this isn't
fantasy.

00:51:04.328 --> 00:51:05.729 align:middle line:90%
This stuff is real.

00:51:05.729 --> 00:51:08.265 align:middle line:84%
Yes and the more that we know
that,

00:51:08.265 --> 00:51:10.100 align:middle line:90%
the more that we recognize that,

00:51:10.100 --> 00:51:13.037 align:middle line:84%
when we're thinking or in
traffic or

00:51:13.037 --> 00:51:15.105 align:middle line:84%
having actions with other
people,

00:51:15.105 --> 00:51:17.741 align:middle line:84%
and we realize that we're just
spirit--

00:51:17.741 --> 00:51:19.543 align:middle line:84%
Yes, spirit having a physical
experience.

00:51:19.543 --> 00:51:21.578 align:middle line:84%
And these experiences, like
sitting in a car,

00:51:21.578 --> 00:51:23.747 align:middle line:84%
it's a wonderful opportunity
for you

00:51:23.747 --> 00:51:25.215 align:middle line:90%
to remember who you are.

00:51:25.215 --> 00:51:26.750 align:middle line:84%
When you want to yell at the
person in front of you,

00:51:26.750 --> 00:51:29.954 align:middle line:84%
stop and breathe, go back to
your center.

00:51:29.954 --> 00:51:32.222 align:middle line:84%
This is an opportunity to show
love.

00:51:32.222 --> 00:51:33.924 align:middle line:84%
So, with your thoughts, send
love to that person.

00:51:33.924 --> 00:51:35.326 align:middle line:90%
I say "pink-light" them.

00:51:35.326 --> 00:51:36.660 align:middle line:90%
Put a pink light around them.

00:51:36.660 --> 00:51:37.561 align:middle line:90%
Love them.

00:51:37.561 --> 00:51:38.595 align:middle line:90%
That's a good way.

00:51:38.595 --> 00:51:40.531 align:middle line:84%
We also have a photo of you
with Cesar Milan,

00:51:40.531 --> 00:51:43.901 align:middle line:84%
who I think is an amazing
animal communicator.

00:51:43.901 --> 00:51:44.601 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:51:44.601 --> 00:51:45.836 align:middle line:90%
Cesar Milan was on the show.

00:51:45.836 --> 00:51:47.204 align:middle line:84%
He did an episode of "Ghost
Whisperer."

00:51:47.204 --> 00:51:49.073 align:middle line:84%
He's as tall as I am, which I
love because

00:51:49.073 --> 00:51:51.742 align:middle line:84%
not many people are also five
foot five.

00:51:51.742 --> 00:51:53.677 align:middle line:84%
Nice man and he has definitely
a link

00:51:53.677 --> 00:51:55.546 align:middle line:84%
with the animal kingdom, no
doubt about it.

00:51:55.546 --> 00:51:56.780 align:middle line:90%
He does.

00:51:56.780 --> 00:51:57.481 align:middle line:90%
Oh, no doubt about it.

00:51:57.481 --> 00:51:58.983 align:middle line:84%
He's a great animal
communicator.

00:51:58.983 --> 00:52:02.286 align:middle line:84%
So, his gifts are beyond just
experience.

00:52:02.286 --> 00:52:04.054 align:middle line:84%
I think so, I definitely think
so.

00:52:04.054 --> 00:52:06.090 align:middle line:84%
Lisa, let me just jump in here
and say

00:52:06.090 --> 00:52:07.224 align:middle line:90%
when animals communicate,

00:52:07.224 --> 00:52:08.425 align:middle line:84%
because people often ask me
that,

00:52:08.425 --> 00:52:10.427 align:middle line:84%
they come through all the time
and they are

00:52:10.427 --> 00:52:12.863 align:middle line:84%
incredible communicators
because when they come through

00:52:12.863 --> 00:52:16.100 align:middle line:84%
they come through with such
purity and

00:52:16.100 --> 00:52:17.568 align:middle line:90%
such unconditional love.

00:52:17.568 --> 00:52:19.103 align:middle line:90%
There's no human stuff in there.

00:52:19.103 --> 00:52:20.204 align:middle line:90%
There's no judgements.

00:52:20.204 --> 00:52:21.271 align:middle line:90%
There's none of that.

00:52:21.271 --> 00:52:22.873 align:middle line:84%
So, what would a message sound
like from an animal?

00:52:22.873 --> 00:52:25.242 align:middle line:84%
For instance, I was doing a
demonstration,

00:52:25.242 --> 00:52:28.445 align:middle line:84%
a workshop, I think it was in
Denver,

00:52:28.445 --> 00:52:31.415 align:middle line:84%
and the lady is standing there
asking a question.

00:52:31.415 --> 00:52:33.984 align:middle line:84%
Right away I see this horse
come next to her.

00:52:33.984 --> 00:52:36.286 align:middle line:84%
It was a brown and white horse
and then I said,

00:52:36.286 --> 00:52:39.957 align:middle line:84%
"There's a man to your left and
he's wearing overalls,"

00:52:39.957 --> 00:52:41.825 align:middle line:90%
and I said his name is William.

00:52:41.825 --> 00:52:44.528 align:middle line:84%
She said, "That's my horse,
that's my Uncle William.

00:52:44.528 --> 00:52:45.963 align:middle line:84%
"He bought me a horse when I
was fourteen and

00:52:45.963 --> 00:52:47.731 align:middle line:90%
"that's the horse he bought me."

00:52:47.731 --> 00:52:48.999 align:middle line:90%
The horse gave me thoughts,

00:52:48.999 --> 00:52:51.402 align:middle line:84%
like telepathic thoughts about
the ribbons,

00:52:51.402 --> 00:52:54.571 align:middle line:84%
the bridle, about how she used
to take care of the horse

00:52:54.571 --> 00:52:57.741 align:middle line:84%
and brush the horse, where the
brush was located still.

00:52:57.741 --> 00:52:59.376 align:middle line:90%
Just these little things.

00:52:59.376 --> 00:53:02.479 align:middle line:84%
The amount of love that the
horse wanted to convey,

00:53:02.479 --> 00:53:04.181 align:middle line:90%
thanking her, the gratitude.

00:53:04.181 --> 00:53:06.717 align:middle line:84%
Animals come through, doggies
all the time,

00:53:06.717 --> 00:53:09.620 align:middle line:84%
cats all the time, they come
through with so much love

00:53:09.620 --> 00:53:11.422 align:middle line:90%
and they thank their loved one.

00:53:11.422 --> 00:53:13.223 align:middle line:90%
I've had many people say,

00:53:13.223 --> 00:53:14.992 align:middle line:84%
"I had to put my baby to sleep,
my doggy to sleep."

00:53:14.992 --> 00:53:18.128 align:middle line:84%
It's a wonderful experience of
an example of

00:53:18.128 --> 00:53:20.230 align:middle line:84%
unconditional love, because it
came from loving that

00:53:20.230 --> 00:53:23.600 align:middle line:84%
animal so much and that's
again, another lesson.

00:53:23.600 --> 00:53:24.601 align:middle line:90%
We always have lessons.

00:53:24.601 --> 00:53:26.370 align:middle line:84%
Every day we have lessons to
learn.

00:53:26.370 --> 00:53:28.272 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my goodness, it's true.

00:53:28.272 --> 00:53:30.507 align:middle line:84%
And if you look at things that
way,

00:53:30.507 --> 00:53:32.209 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the pain, the physical
experience

00:53:32.209 --> 00:53:34.144 align:middle line:90%
of putting an animal down versus

00:53:34.144 --> 00:53:39.149 align:middle line:84%
the spiritual experience of
looking at the entire soul

00:53:39.450 --> 00:53:41.085 align:middle line:90%
group that you had together,

00:53:41.085 --> 00:53:44.054 align:middle line:84%
it really, it takes the edge
off a little bit.

00:53:44.054 --> 00:53:47.057 align:middle line:84%
It's also, Lisa, I say with
everything in life,

00:53:47.057 --> 00:53:48.792 align:middle line:84%
it's always the motivation
behind the act

00:53:48.792 --> 00:53:50.461 align:middle line:90%
so whenever there's a situation,

00:53:50.461 --> 00:53:52.896 align:middle line:84%
what is the motivation for you
behind that situation?

00:53:52.896 --> 00:53:55.199 align:middle line:84%
Is it coming from a pure place
of unconditional love

00:53:55.199 --> 00:53:57.101 align:middle line:84%
trying to do the best you can
do?

00:53:57.101 --> 00:53:57.968 align:middle line:90%
Is that where it's coming from?

00:53:57.968 --> 00:53:59.970 align:middle line:84%
Then you're good, that's where
it should be.

00:53:59.970 --> 00:54:01.305 align:middle line:90%
But if it's a place of

00:54:01.305 --> 00:54:03.440 align:middle line:84%
"I need to get ahead, I need to
get over on that person,

00:54:03.440 --> 00:54:04.641 align:middle line:90%
"I need to be--"

00:54:04.641 --> 00:54:05.742 align:middle line:90%
That's not the right space.

00:54:05.742 --> 00:54:06.643 align:middle line:90%
It's about inclusion.

00:54:06.643 --> 00:54:09.113 align:middle line:84%
It's about being inclusive and
out of that place

00:54:09.113 --> 00:54:10.747 align:middle line:90%
of competition and fear.

00:54:10.747 --> 00:54:13.117 align:middle line:90%
And treating another person.

00:54:13.117 --> 00:54:13.984 align:middle line:90%
It's the Golden Rule.

00:54:13.984 --> 00:54:15.786 align:middle line:84%
I tell you that I love this,
it's so true.

00:54:15.786 --> 00:54:17.254 align:middle line:90%
Give another person.

00:54:17.254 --> 00:54:18.755 align:middle line:84%
Treat them the way you want to
be treated.

00:54:18.755 --> 00:54:20.057 align:middle line:90%
Say things to them.

00:54:20.057 --> 00:54:22.226 align:middle line:90%
I'm known, in New York probably,

00:54:22.226 --> 00:54:24.027 align:middle line:90%
around the country but,

00:54:24.027 --> 00:54:26.096 align:middle line:84%
I always change the energy in a
space.

00:54:26.096 --> 00:54:27.798 align:middle line:90%
I know you do the same thing.

00:54:27.798 --> 00:54:30.033 align:middle line:84%
When I go into a space, like a
Starbucks,

00:54:30.033 --> 00:54:31.502 align:middle line:84%
and they're all standing there
like this,

00:54:31.502 --> 00:54:32.569 align:middle line:90%
pulling up the cups and I'm like

00:54:32.569 --> 00:54:34.238 align:middle line:84%
"Hi, how are you? What are you
doing?"

00:54:34.238 --> 00:54:35.772 align:middle line:90%
I make it fun for them.

00:54:35.772 --> 00:54:38.208 align:middle line:84%
I engage them and I think it's
very very important

00:54:38.208 --> 00:54:40.744 align:middle line:84%
that we remember as spiritual
beings,

00:54:40.744 --> 00:54:42.112 align:middle line:90%
we need to engage each other.

00:54:42.112 --> 00:54:43.647 align:middle line:90%
We're sharing the space.

00:54:43.647 --> 00:54:44.848 align:middle line:90%
Let's have fun with each other.

00:54:44.848 --> 00:54:46.783 align:middle line:84%
I do that with laughter and
some people

00:54:46.783 --> 00:54:48.218 align:middle line:84%
have said, "She giggles too
much,"

00:54:48.218 --> 00:54:51.121 align:middle line:84%
but I intentionally bring
